Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

this little bit of code looks good, have one suggestion, I would also like to know how you plan to implement the add function. User passes a file to upload to store, what do you do with it, is there a cinder api you are planning to use for this? Also on the get what are you planning to return the url to cinder? For example, how would nova then use the info in glance get to clone and boot the cloned volume?

Patch Set 2:

found this using your commit message as clues: https://etherpad.openstack.org/volume-host-attaching

is the plan for add this: create volume, attach from glance host, stream file content to local device, then detach? Will there be any limitation on cinder backends that will support this?
